summary: This code imports the Highs solver from highspy library, reads a MPS file into the solver, runs the optimization, and prints the model status.

details.comment: This code imports the Highs solver from highspy library, reads a MPS file into the solver, runs the optimization, and prints the model status.
details.content:
import highspy
h = highspy.Highs()
filename = 'exported.mps'
h.readModel(filename)
h.run()
print('Model ', filename, ' has status ', h.getModelStatus())
